Package compiler.symboltable

Enum SymbolType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<SymbolType>
compiler.symboltable.SymbolType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<SymbolType>, java.lang.constant.Constable
public enum SymbolType extends Enum<SymbolType>
The Type of a Symbol found in a high-level-language program. Symbols may represent Variables, Constants or Labels and have the corresponding type. The Type is determined using a regular expression that a Symbol must match. The assert methods use them and may throw an CompmilerException associated with each type when the assertion fails.
Author:
Alex Mandelias
